          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1659889654794-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1659889654794-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1659889654794-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat, then boil half a kettle</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Cook for 6-8 min or until golden, stirring frequently, then transfer to a plate (reserve the pan for later!) – this is your <strong>golden panko</strong></p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1659889657964-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
