    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the reserved pan to a medium-high heat and add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Wash your <strong>cavolo nero</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once fragrant, tear the <strong>cavolo nero</strong> into the pan (discard any tough stalks) with a splash of<strong> cold water</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until starting to wilt</p>",
